		<title>07Pig Units in rural Sowerby</title>
		<content>     There are several of these        
 intensive rearing pig units in our    
 block. A one man unit contains 70 sows
 with 3 boars in use producing 24      
 piglets per sow per year resulting in 
 1500 piglets per year. They are weaned
 at 3 weeks old and on reaching 65_70  
 Kilos live weight they are taken to   
 the local fatstock market. They are   
 sold for 80p per Kilo. The pens are   
 concrete and straw and the effluent   
 is contained in a tank and spread on  
 the land by a slurry tanker.          
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
